$interpreted: Zola: ...Where am I? How did I suddenly...
Charle: This is the Rune Academy's battle simulation arena.
Charle: All we need to do to keep the injuries outside to a minimum is to trap you and the Soul Energy you attract in here.
Zola: You think these minuscule magic circles for your young, bumbling students can stop me!?
Charle: That's why——I'm here!
Zola: Hehe, alrighty then〜
Zola: Actually, I'd like to see if you're worthy of sacrificing yourself, if you can really save them from joining you in the grave!
Zola: You, the Rune Academy, Carlos, and everyone else!
Zola: All that hurt my sister must die!
Charle: Doing this on my own...I still can't do it?
???: Cut the crap, who's always been babbling on about how important cooperation is?
???: Didn't think you'd try to do everything yourself, you freakin' idiot.
Charle: That voice...!?
Charle: Mo...rris, it's you...!?
Morris: Besides me, is there anyone else who's capable of getting involved with your magic?
Charle: .......
Charle: Indeed, there is no one else.
Charle: I really missed you, partner.
Morris: .......
Morris: ......Hmph, you're getting pretty old yourself.
Morris: Save the disgusting talk for later; first let's take care of this Dracontine monkey!
Zola: So ANNOYING!! Each one of you is more annoying than the last!
Zola: I'll kill you all!
Morris: The masters of Life Magic and Applied Magic have joined forces. If you think you can do it, give it a try!
Zola: Shir...ley...
Charle: So, your body was reconstructed, or...
Morris: How would that happen, you dummy.
Morris: As soon as I entered this space, I was forced to separate with him.
Morris: Based on my speculations, the "me" that you see before your eyes is a body made of pure Soul Energy.
Charle: A body of Soul Energy...? Ah, so you mean...!
Morris: That's right. Your adopted son and I are two totally different Soul Energies; we were only linked by forced reincarnation.
Morris: Entering this space and being affected by this chaotic Soul Energy, our individual Soul Energies returned to their proper state.
Charle: And, Elio's consciousness...
Morris: It remains. It was merely forced into a pseudo-death state.
Morris: Once he sees you, his body will burst forth with intertwined...
Charle: ...I'm not worthy to be a father...
Morris: What now!?
Charle: Look! The Soul Energy has not yet dissipated, instead——
Morris: The backlash...
Morris: Dammit, I didn't calculate the effects that the runes on that Dracontine monkey's body would have!
Charle: Morris! Elio!
Charle: (If we're going to suppress chaotic Soul Energy that's this massive, we'll need to use an equal amount of Soul Energy to cancel it out.)
Charle: (If I use this body of mine that never ages...)
Charle: Hold on, I'm coming!
Morris: ...*gasp*...
Charle: (Oh no! My Soul Energy is insufficient! If this continues, both of them won't be saved!)
Morris: ...Charle...
Charle: Rays of light...Morris!
Morris: Hmph, it looks like I won't be able to tell you about the intel I got from that Dracontine monkey...you'll have to ask Clovis.
Charle: What are you doing, Morris!?
Morris: And it was I who burnt down the Library of Forbidden Texts. You'll have to rebuild it.
Morris: I had merely researched it all, but you've committed it all to memory. Isn't that right, Bookworm Ceres?
Charle: You're using your Soul Energy to cancel it out...
Charle: Stop Morris! If you do this, your soul will dissipate completely!
Morris: Hmph, well would you like to sacrifice your son?
Charle: I...
Morris: ...Hmph, I'll give you two some time.
Morris: I knew you wouldn't be able to choose, so I've chosen for you.
Morris: ......Partner.
